{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-03-21T10:10+0000", "md5": "0559393A99DB45FD61052D479E699AB9", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee-Pro", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee-Pro", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 10}, "context": "ZigBee-Pro is a version of ZigBee that benefits from higher capacities as the routing techniques, the network of jumps, the maximal number of peripherals as well as the security of the network. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.303455352783203e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013265609741210938}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.303455352783203e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013265609741210938}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 10}, "context": "The ZigBee network has three kinds of modules, namely End Device which is a terminal node (e.g., sensor, actuator), Router which routes and transmits the data between the devices and enables one to expand the physical range of a ZigBee network, and Coordinator which manages the high-level functions of the network as the authentification and security. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007440447807312012}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.002522289752960205}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 10}, "context": "The ZigBee protocol is based on this standard for the physical layer (PHY) and the medium access control (MAC).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.008185803890228271}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005068778991699219}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 5, "offsetEnd": 11}, "context": "In a ZigBee network, there is necessarily a coordinator.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00019103288650512695}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.3272972106933594e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 27, "offsetEnd": 33}, "context": "ZigBee-Pro is a version of ZigBee that benefits from higher capacities as the routing techniques, the network of jumps, the maximal number of peripherals as well as the security of the network. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.303455352783203e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013265609741210938}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 29, "offsetEnd": 35}, "context": "In the system developed, the ZigBee-Pro network between the collector node and the gateway is configured with a star topology, using the ISM frequency band at 2.4 GHz. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.003947138786315918}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.15972524881362915}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Atmega328-AU", "normalizedForm": "Atmega328-AU", "offsetStart": 53, "offsetEnd": 65}, "publisher": {"rawForm": "Microchip", "normalizedForm": "Microchip", "offsetStart": 67, "offsetEnd": 76}, "context": "The collector node is built around a microcontroller Atmega328-AU (Microchip) running at 8 MHz. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9280455112457275}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0062392354011535645}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9280455112457275}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0062392354011535645}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 81, "offsetEnd": 87}, "context": "The collector node has, therefore, two antennas, a LoRa antenna at 868 MHz and a ZigBee antenna at 2.4 GHz, see Figure 5.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.03470039367675781}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00012755393981933594}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 100, "offsetEnd": 106}, "context": "When accessible, the collector node communicates in Zig-Bee with the remote gateway equipped with a ZigBee module.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.04425656795501709}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00014972686767578125}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 102, "offsetEnd": 108}, "context": "We chose to base the wireless communication AIR2AIR between the data collector and the gateway on the ZigBee protocol [35].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.914138793945312e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35, "offsetStart": 13871, "offsetEnd": 13875}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 109, "offsetEnd": 115}, "context": "As presented in Figure 2, we propose an architecture based on two radio communication links, namely LoRa and ZigBee.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.000272214412689209}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 115, "offsetEnd": 121}, "context": "The data frames are transmitted via a LoRa communication and delivered at the end of the flight to a gateway via a ZigBee communication.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.972131609916687}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.593631744384766e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 116, "offsetEnd": 122}, "context": "It is equipped with a LoRa radio module RFM95W (HopeRF) enabling to communicate with the buried sensor nodes, and a ZigBee radio module Xbee-PRO (Digi International) to exchange with the server through the gateway.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.010572612285614014}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002989768981933594}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.344650268554688e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 175, "offsetEnd": 181}, "context": "The network layer (NMK) and the application layer (APL) are defined and maintained by the enterprise organization known as the Connectivity Standards Alliance (CSA), formerly ZigBee Alliance.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8637137413024902}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00040477514266967773}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.430511474609375e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 186, "offsetEnd": 192}, "context": "We developed a collector node including two radio modules: the first one is devoted to the communication in LoRa with the buried sensor nodes, and the second one to the communication in ZigBee with the gateway.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.7220458984375e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9981145858764648}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ZigBee", "normalizedForm": "ZigBee", "offsetStart": 229, "offsetEnd": 235}, "context": "The ZigBee network has three kinds of modules, namely End Device which is a terminal node (e.g., sensor, actuator), Router which routes and transmits the data between the devices and enables one to expand the physical range of a ZigBee network, and Coordinator which manages the high-level functions of the network as the authentification and security.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007440447807312012}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.002522289752960205}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998929500579834}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998800754547119}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[35]", "normalizedForm": "[35]", "refKey": 35}]}], "references": [{"refKey": 35, "tei": "<biblStruct xml:id=\"b35\">\n\t<analytic>\n\t\t<title level=\"a\" type=\"main\">Study on ZigBee technology</title>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">C</forename><surname>Muthu Ramya</surname></persName>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">M</forename><surname>Shanmugaraj</surname></persName>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">R</forename><surname>Prabakaran</surname></persName>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<idno type=\"DOI\">10.1109/ICECTECH.2011.5942102</